##International flights at Beijing airport will be diverted to Shijiazhuang, Tianjin and other places, as well as 14 other news items, the commission's investigation team said

According to Dr. Syzygium Aromaticum, as of 22:19 on March 19, there were 7,452 confirmed cases in China, bringing the total to 81,263, including 190 imported cases. There were 2314 severe cases, 3250 deaths and 70561 cured cases.

With the exception of China, there are 121954 confirmed cases, 143156 confirmed cases, 5,989 deaths and 15,213 cures. With the exception of China, at least 166 countries and regions have reported confirmed cases. A state of emergency has been declared in more than 40 countries.

Development of epidemic situation

In Italy, 475 people died in one day. As of 1800 hours Rome time on 18 March, Italy had 4207 new confirmed cases and 475 new deaths, the highest number of deaths in a single day in the world. According to the Johns Hopkins University, the mortality rate in Italy is 8.3% and rising, surpassing 6.5% in Iran, 4.3% in Spain and 4.0% in China. Death cases are still concentrated in the elderly, with the median age of death cases being 63 years, with an average age of 79.5 years. Italy has imposed a nationwide blockade since March 10, originally scheduled to be lifted on March 25, Prime Minister Contes said on the 19th, due to the current situation, blockade measures will continue to be extended. In addition to Italy, the Czech Republic, France, Spain and Belgium are also blockaded.

Beijing imported cases accounted for 34% of the country, nearly 80% of transit. As of 2400 hours on March 18, Beijing has reported 64 confirmed cases imported from abroad, 78% of which were transit passengers and 42% were international students. Beijing Capital International Airport has about 6,000 to 8,000 visitors a day, according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. "since the introduction of imported cases on February 29,2,417 people have been screened by the Customs and Quarantine authorities at the airport for transfer to medical institutions, averaging 127 per day. In the past week, the daily average has reached 288 people and the daily average reached 479 on the 18th. "

New cases of pneumonia in China appear for the first time. On March 18, there was the first zero increase in the number of newly diagnosed cases of new coronary pneumonia in China. The 34 new cases reported in mainland China on Wednesday were all imported cases, according to the Chinese Health Commission. But China is not out of the woods yet. Experts say the outbreak will not be truly over until there are no new infections for at least 14 days. It remains to be seen whether the virus will reappear once daily life around the country resumes and travel restrictions are lifted.

Nearly 10,000 new cases have been confirmed in the United States, and Donald Trump signed into law a second new Crown Disease Response Plan. Donald Trump signs "bailout package. " . The program includes free testing of new crowns, increased paid leave benefits, and increased food subsidies for the elderly and children. In addition, Congress is drafting a third stimulus package of about $1 trillion for the new outbreak, including a total of $500 billion in direct cash handouts to affected Americans, providing loans to affected industries such as airlines and hotels, as well as small businesses.

Future Studies

Tu Youyou: Africa should be prepared to prevent new crown from being misdiagnosed as malaria. On March 16,14 experts from China, Germany and the United Kingdom published a review article in The Lancet Medical Journal titled "It is critical that malaria outbreak areas be prepared for a new crown pandemic. ". The article argues that malaria endemic areas need not only to take measures against the new coronavirus, but also to prevent the outbreak of the new coronavirus outbreak of malaria control work may be caused by the damage. The corresponding author is Tu Youyou, chief scientist of the Chinese Academy of Traditional Chinese medicine. The lessons of the 2014-2016 Zaire ebolavirus epidemic are worth learning.

Urban Prevention and control

Beijing CDC advises foreign students not to return to China. On the afternoon of March 18, at a press conference on "the prevention and control of the new crown pneumonia epidemic in Beijing" , Pang Xinghuo, deputy director of the Center for Disease Control and Prevention, suggested that "foreign students should not be allowed to return to their home countries for a while. " Indeed, there is a need to return home by direct flights as far as possible. One of the most popular comments on Weibo,@renmin Ribao, came from an overseas student, who said he had "caused trouble for the motherland" by returning to China, "waited until classes were suspended" and "we did our best when the epidemic was at its worst" .

Inbound flights from Beijing Capital International Airport are diverted to airports in Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan and Hohhot. According to Caixin and other media reports, from the evening of March 18, originally scheduled inbound flights from Beijing Capital International Airport were diverted to the airports of Tianjin, Shijiazhuang, Taiyuan and Hohhot. After passengers were tested, those who were healthy were then transferred to Beijing, those at risk are treated locally. Foreign Airlines are holding off.

On March 19, CAAC announced the first batch of Adjustment Program: March 20 Moscow to Beijing CA910 flight, March 22 Paris to Beijing CA934 Flight First Entry Point for Tianjin; The first entry point for flight CA926 from Tokyo to Beijing will be Hohhot from March 20 to 22, and the first entry point for flight HU7976 from Toronto to Beijing will be Taiyuan from March 21 to 22(the above dates are China Standard Time) .

All foreign visitors to Beijing will be under observation for 14 days and will no longer be required to apply for home quarantine. On March 18, Beijing issued a circular on further tightening control measures for personnel entering Beijing from abroad. The notice said that from now on, all foreign visitors to Beijing should be transferred to a central observation point for 14 days of medical observation at their own expense. If it is not suitable to focus observation on the elderly aged 70 years or above, minors aged 14 years or below, pregnant women and parturients, and those suffering from basic diseases, etc. , after strict assessment, they may be observed at home. In the early hours of March 19, the Office of the Leading Group for the prevention and control of the epidemic of new crown pneumonia in Beijing announced that it would no longer accept applications for home observation from people who live alone and have no other residents in their homes.

Wuhan allows residents of epidemic-free residential areas to move in batches. Wuhan New Crown Pneumonia Epidemic Prevention and Control Headquarters Community Epidemic Prevention and Control Group today (19) issued the opinion of adjusting control measures: residents are allowed to be divided into groups, time periods, building blocks, non-clustered individual activities are carried out in the residential area; residents are allowed to engage in non-clustered individual free activities in the residential area if the residential area is designated as epidemic-free and for a continuous period of more than 7 days. The villages (teams) without epidemic situation can restore the order of villagers'life and carry out agricultural production in an orderly manner.

Hubei Personnel Return to work only health code. At a press conference in Hubei Province on the afternoon of March 18, Cao Guangjing, vice governor of Hubei Province, introduced the progress of the resumption of work and production in Hubei Province. He said that support for enterprises should be strengthened, to coordinate and solve the outstanding problems in the resumption of work and production in time. "When it comes to staff returning to work, people report that there are certain difficulties. The main problem is that the mobility of personnel in the province requires a large number of documents to be submitted and is difficult to declare, " Cao said, in Hubei Province, it has been made clear that no conditions can be attached to the movement of people other than the health code. "The movement of people across the province by virtue of the Health Code can not be subject to any other conditions. " However, hubei Province personnel to leave Hubei Province need to deal with the provincial acceptance of the certification materials. "We urge our sister provinces and cities to give care and support to the migrant workers in low-and medium-risk cities in Hubei Province. We also hope that our sister provinces and cities will not impose additional conditions on the migrant workers in low-and medium-risk areas and those with health codes in Hubei Province, " Cao said.

Medical Solution

World Health Organization launches global clinical trial of new coronavirus. On the 19th, World Health Organization announced that it would launch a global large clinical trial of Covid-19, known as the SOLIDARITY trial. In each of the control and four treatment groups, patients in the control group received standard care in their home country, while the other four treatment groups received standard care in addition to standard care, use Radicivir, Lopinavir Ritonavir, Lopinavir Ritonavir + Interferon (IFN -) or chloroquine. Argentina, Bahrain, Canada, France, Iran, Norway, South Africa, Spain, Switzerland and Thailand have confirmed their accession.

Study found that anti-aids drugs treatment of new crown has no significant effect. The results of the Lopinavir Litteau clinical trial conducted by Cao Bin's team, vice president of the China Japan Friendship Hospital, were disclosed on March 19, lopinavir and Ritonavir did not significantly improve clinical outcomes, did not significantly reduce mortality, did not reduce viral load in the pharynx, and were relatively more likely to have gastrointestinal adverse events. The study, published online in the Journal The New England Journal of Medicine, was led by Cao Bin, who is collaborating on the Litteau trial at Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital. The efficacy of Lopinavir and Litteau against neocoronavirus has been previously rejected by several experts.

Peripheral influence

The Foreign Ministry has asked foreign journalists from the New York Times, The Wall Street Journal and the Washington Post to leave China. On March 18, the Ministry of Foreign Affairs responded to the "February 2020 designation of five Chinese media organizations in the United States as foreign missions" and other incidents, announcing the three requirements: "The Voice of America, " "The New York Times, " "The Wall Street Journal, " "The Washington Post, " and "The Times" will provide financial information of all staff members to the Chinese side; US journalists from the New York Times, The Wall Street Journal and the Washington Post shall submit their names to the Information Department of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs within 4 days, return their press cards within 10 days, and shall not be allowed to work as journalists in China (including Hong Kong and Macao) ; Restrictions will be imposed on U. S. journalists in areas such as visas, administrative review, and interviews.

The new crown outbreak has led to the suspension of 850m students, half of the global student body. According to the United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural Organization, as of March 17, more than 850 million children and adolescents worldwide, about half of the world's total, had suspended classes because of the new pneumonia outbreak. It is reported that the global 102 countries and regions have suspended all classes, and another 11 countries and regions partial suspension. That number is expected to continue to grow.

Gansu Market Supervision Bureau requires cadres to take the lead in eating out and spend no less than 200 yuan a week. On March 19, the Gansu Provincial Bureau of market supervision issued a proposal that cadres and workers should take the lead in consumption and support the catering industry to tide over the difficulties: 1. Party members and leading cadres should take the lead in "eating out" to demonstrate their social responsibility through concrete actions. No less than 200 yuan per week. 2. Encourage cadres, workers and relatives to take the lead in "eating and drinking" , and guide and motivate the masses around them to restore consumer confidence as soon as possible. 3, take the lead in using "public chopsticks, " the promotion of civilized table. 4. Strict integrity rules, and individual consumers pay.

The media attention

Investigation team of State Supervision Commission Announces Investigation of Li Wenliang. At 7 pm on March 19, CCTV news announced the investigation of Li Wenliang by the State Supervision and Administration Commission. Internal issues include Li Wenliang's posting on Wechat, receiving reprimands, getting sick, rescuing and dealing with the aftermath, as well as answering questions from reporters. The final recommendation is that "due to the improper letter of reprimand issued by the Zhongnan Road Police Station and the irregular law enforcement procedures, the investigation team has recommended that the Wuhan supervisory authorities in Hubei Province supervise and rectify the matter, urge the Public Security Bureau to revoke the letter of reprimand and hold the relevant personnel accountable, and announce the results of the settlement to the public in a timely manner. "
